Note: ============================================================================
Note: EMITTER COMMON - Shared Byte-Buffer Foundation for HIR Translation Backends
Note: ============================================================================
Note: Provides the canonical EmitterContext type and shared helpers used by all
Note: HIR-to-target-language emitters. Internally backed by a raw byte buffer
Note: that grows geometrically, giving amortized O(1) append performance (the
Note: previous implementation rebuilt a String on every emit, costing O(n^2)
Note: in the size of the accumulated output).
Note: Two parallel APIs are exposed:
Note:   1. EmitterContext (Runa struct) - high-level API consumed by
Note:      hir_to_julia.runa and any other backend that prefers to carry
Note:      indentation / line-column / error state in a typed context.
Note:   2. Raw 24-byte buffer header (Integer pointer) - low-level API used by
Note:      the 33+ per-language byte-buffer emitters (c_emitter.runa,
Note:      python_emitter.runa, ...). Layout:
Note:           offset 0  - buffer pointer  (Integer)
Note:           offset 8  - buffer capacity (Integer, bytes)
Note:           offset 16 - buffer length   (Integer, bytes written)
Note: Both APIs share the same growth, indent and reset semantics so a backend
Note: can use whichever fits its existing structure best.
Note: ============================================================================

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as MemoryCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as ListCore

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Constant EMITTER_INITIAL_CAPACITY as Integer is 4096
Constant EMITTER_HEADER_SIZE as Integer is 24
Constant EMITTER_OFFSET_BUFFER as Integer is 0
Constant EMITTER_OFFSET_CAPACITY as Integer is 8
Constant EMITTER_OFFSET_LENGTH as Integer is 16
Constant EMITTER_NEWLINE_BYTE as Integer is 10
Constant EMITTER_SPACE_BYTE as Integer is 32
Constant EMITTER_TAB_BYTE as Integer is 9

Note: ============================================================================
Note: EMITTER CONTEXT (high-level struct API)
Note: ============================================================================
Note: Canonical context carried through every emit_* call in a high-level
Note: backend. Wraps a raw byte buffer in `output_buffer` so all string
Note: appends are O(amortized 1) rather than O(n).
Note: Fields:
Note:   output_buffer   - Integer pointer to raw byte buffer (heap-allocated)
Note:   output_capacity - capacity of the byte buffer (bytes)
Note:   output_length   - bytes currently written to the buffer
Note:   indent_level    - logical nesting depth
Note:   indent_size     - spaces per nesting level (typical: 2 or 4)
Note:   use_tabs        - 1 if indent should use tabs, 0 for spaces
Note:   current_line    - 1-based line number in output_buffer (post-emit)
Note:   current_column  - 1-based column number in output_buffer (post-emit)
Note:   line_start      - 1 if next emit begins a fresh line (so indent is needed)
Note:   errors          - List of emitter error messages
Note:   warnings        - List of emitter warning messages
Note:   had_error       - 1 if any error was recorded
Note: ============================================================================
Type called "EmitterContext":
    output_buffer as Integer
    output_capacity as Integer
    output_length as Integer
    indent_level as Integer
    indent_size as Integer
    use_tabs as Integer
    current_line as Integer
    current_column as Integer
    line_start as Integer
    errors as List[String]
    warnings as List[String]
    had_error as Integer
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: RAW BUFFER PRIMITIVES
Note: ============================================================================
Note: These operate on the 24-byte header layout described above and are
Note: shared between the struct API (which embeds the header in EmitterContext)
Note: and per-language byte-buffer emitters which use the layout directly.
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Grow a raw header so it has room for `needed` additional bytes beyond
Note: the current length. Returns 1 on success, 0 on allocation failure.
Note: Doubles capacity (and keeps doubling) until the request fits.
Process called "emitter_raw_ensure_capacity" takes header as Integer, needed as Integer returns Integer:
    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with header, EMITTER_OFFSET_CAPACITY
    Let length be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with header, EMITTER_OFFSET_LENGTH

    Let available be capacity minus length
    If available is greater than or equal to needed:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let new_capacity be capacity multiplied by 2
    If new_capacity is less than capacity plus needed:
        Set new_capacity to capacity plus needed
    End If
    While new_capacity minus length is less than needed:
        Set new_capacity to new_capacity multiplied by 2
    End While

    Let new_buffer be proc allocate from Layout with new_capacity
    If new_buffer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let old_buffer be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with header, EMITTER_OFFSET_BUFFER
    If length is greater than 0:
        proc memory_copy from MemoryCore with new_buffer, old_buffer, length
    End If

    If old_buffer is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with old_buffer
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with header, EMITTER_OFFSET_BUFFER, new_buffer
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with header, EMITTER_OFFSET_CAPACITY, new_capacity
    Return 1
End Process

Note: Append a single byte to the raw buffer. Returns 1 on success.
Process called "emitter_raw_emit_byte" takes header as Integer, byte_value as Integer returns Integer:
    Let success be proc emitter_raw_ensure_capacity with header, 1
    If success is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let buffer be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with header, EMITTER_OFFSET_BUFFER
    Let length be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with header, EMITTER_OFFSET_LENGTH
    proc memory_set_byte from MemoryCore with buffer, length, byte_value
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with header, EMITTER_OFFSET_LENGTH, length plus 1
    Return 1
End Process

Note: Append the bytes of a null-terminated string to the raw buffer.
Note: A null str pointer or empty string is a no-op returning 1.
Process called "emitter_raw_emit_string" takes header as Integer, str as Integer returns Integer:
    If str is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let str_length be proc string_length from StringCore with str
    If str_length is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let success be proc emitter_raw_ensure_capacity with header, str_length
    If success is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let buffer be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with header, EMITTER_OFFSET_BUFFER
    Let length be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with header, EMITTER_OFFSET_LENGTH

    Note: memory_copy uses absolute pointers; offset the destination so we
    Note: append after existing content. The source string is read from
    Note: offset 0 of `str`.
    Let dest_ptr be buffer plus length
    proc memory_copy from MemoryCore with dest_ptr, str, str_length

    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with header, EMITTER_OFFSET_LENGTH, length plus str_length
    Return 1
End Process

Note: Allocate and initialize a raw 24-byte header backed by a fresh
Note: initial-capacity byte buffer. Returns the header pointer, 0 on failure.
Process called "emitter_raw_create" returns Integer:
    Let header be proc allocate from Layout with EMITTER_HEADER_SIZE
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let buffer be proc allocate from Layout with EMITTER_INITIAL_CAPACITY
    If buffer is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with header
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with header, EMITTER_OFFSET_BUFFER, buffer
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with header, EMITTER_OFFSET_CAPACITY, EMITTER_INITIAL_CAPACITY
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with header, EMITTER_OFFSET_LENGTH, 0
    Return header
End Process

Note: Destroy a raw header by deallocating its byte buffer and the header
Note: itself. Safe to call with a null header (returns 1).
Process called "emitter_raw_destroy" takes header as Integer returns Integer:
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let buffer be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with header, EMITTER_OFFSET_BUFFER
    If buffer is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with buffer
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with header
    Return 1
End Process

Note: Return the current byte length recorded in a raw header.
Process called "emitter_raw_length" takes header as Integer returns Integer:
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with header, EMITTER_OFFSET_LENGTH
End Process

Note: Return a freshly allocated null-terminated copy of the bytes written
Note: to the raw buffer. Caller owns the returned pointer. Returns 0 on
Note: allocation failure or for a null header.
Process called "emitter_raw_get_output" takes header as Integer returns Integer:
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let buffer be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with header, EMITTER_OFFSET_BUFFER
    Let length be proc memory_get_int64 from MemoryCore with header, EMITTER_OFFSET_LENGTH

    Let output be proc allocate from Layout with length plus 1
    If output is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If length is greater than 0:
        proc memory_copy from MemoryCore with output, buffer, length
    End If
    proc memory_set_byte from MemoryCore with output, length, 0
    Return output
End Process

Note: Reset the byte length to 0, keeping the existing allocation. Safe with
Note: a null header.
Process called "emitter_raw_reset" takes header as Integer returns Integer:
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from MemoryCore with header, EMITTER_OFFSET_LENGTH, 0
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: HIGH-LEVEL EMITTERCONTEXT CONSTRUCTOR
Note: ============================================================================
Note: Build a fresh EmitterContext with defaults suitable for most backends.
Note: Default style: 4-space indentation, no tabs. The output buffer starts
Note: at EMITTER_INITIAL_CAPACITY bytes and grows geometrically on demand.
Process called "create_emitter_context" returns EmitterContext:
    Let buf be proc allocate from Layout with EMITTER_INITIAL_CAPACITY
    Let cap be EMITTER_INITIAL_CAPACITY
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Set cap to 0
    End If

    Let ctx be a value of type EmitterContext with
        output_buffer as buf,
        output_capacity as cap,
        output_length as 0,
        indent_level as 0,
        indent_size as 4,
        use_tabs as 0,
        current_line as 1,
        current_column as 1,
        line_start as 1,
        errors as proc list_create from ListCore,
        warnings as proc list_create from ListCore,
        had_error as 0

    Return ctx
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: INTERNAL GROWTH HELPERS (struct API)
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Ensure the context's buffer has room for `needed` additional bytes.
Note: Returns 1 on success, 0 on allocation failure. The caller is expected
Note: to set ctx.had_error / append to ctx.errors if this returns 0.
Process called "emitter_ctx_ensure_capacity" takes ctx as EmitterContext, needed as Integer returns Integer:
    Let available be ctx.output_capacity minus ctx.output_length
    If available is greater than or equal to needed:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let new_capacity be ctx.output_capacity multiplied by 2
    If new_capacity is less than ctx.output_capacity plus needed:
        Set new_capacity to ctx.output_capacity plus needed
    End If
    While new_capacity minus ctx.output_length is less than needed:
        Set new_capacity to new_capacity multiplied by 2
    End While

    Let new_buffer be proc allocate from Layout with new_capacity
    If new_buffer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If ctx.output_length is greater than 0:
        proc memory_copy from MemoryCore with new_buffer, ctx.output_buffer, ctx.output_length
    End If
    If ctx.output_buffer is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with ctx.output_buffer
    End If

    Set ctx.output_buffer to new_buffer
    Set ctx.output_capacity to new_capacity
    Return 1
End Process

Note: Append a single byte to the context buffer, growing as needed.
Process called "emitter_ctx_emit_byte" takes ctx as EmitterContext, byte_value as Integer:
    Let success be proc emitter_ctx_ensure_capacity with ctx, 1
    If success is equal to 0:
        Set ctx.had_error to 1
        proc list_append from ListCore with ctx.errors, "emitter buffer growth failed"
        Return
    End If

    proc memory_set_byte from MemoryCore with ctx.output_buffer, ctx.output_length, byte_value
    Set ctx.output_length to ctx.output_length plus 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: INDENTATION MANAGEMENT
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Increase the nesting depth by 1.
Process called "emitter_indent" takes ctx as EmitterContext:
    Set ctx.indent_level to ctx.indent_level plus 1
End Process

Note: Decrease the nesting depth by 1, clamped at 0.
Process called "emitter_dedent" takes ctx as EmitterContext:
    If ctx.indent_level is greater than 0:
        Set ctx.indent_level to ctx.indent_level minus 1
    End If
End Process

Note: Emit the indentation prefix for the current nesting depth using the
Note: byte buffer. Respects use_tabs and indent_size.
Process called "emitter_emit_indent" takes ctx as EmitterContext:
    If ctx.use_tabs is equal to 1:
        Let level_i be 0
        While level_i is less than ctx.indent_level:
            proc emitter_ctx_emit_byte with ctx, EMITTER_TAB_BYTE
            Set ctx.current_column to ctx.current_column plus 1
            Set level_i to level_i plus 1
        End While
    Otherwise:
        Let total_spaces be ctx.indent_level multiplied by ctx.indent_size
        Let space_i be 0
        While space_i is less than total_spaces:
            proc emitter_ctx_emit_byte with ctx, EMITTER_SPACE_BYTE
            Set space_i to space_i plus 1
        End While
        Set ctx.current_column to ctx.current_column plus total_spaces
    End If

    Set ctx.line_start to 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TEXT EMISSION
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Append raw text to the output buffer. If line_start is set, emits
Note: indentation first. Updates current_line/current_column by scanning the
Note: text for newline characters.
Process called "emitter_emit" takes ctx as EmitterContext, text as String:
    If ctx.line_start is equal to 1:
        proc emitter_emit_indent with ctx
    End If

    If text is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let text_len be proc string_length from StringCore with text
    If text_len is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let success be proc emitter_ctx_ensure_capacity with ctx, text_len
    If success is equal to 0:
        Set ctx.had_error to 1
        proc list_append from ListCore with ctx.errors, "emitter buffer growth failed"
        Return
    End If

    Let dest_ptr be ctx.output_buffer plus ctx.output_length
    proc memory_copy from MemoryCore with dest_ptr, text, text_len
    Set ctx.output_length to ctx.output_length plus text_len

    Note: Scan text for newlines to update line/column counters.
    Let scan_i be 0
    While scan_i is less than text_len:
        Let ch_code be proc string_char_code_at from StringCore with text, scan_i
        If ch_code is equal to EMITTER_NEWLINE_BYTE:
            Set ctx.current_line to ctx.current_line plus 1
            Set ctx.current_column to 1
            Set ctx.line_start to 1
        Otherwise:
            Set ctx.current_column to ctx.current_column plus 1
            Set ctx.line_start to 0
        End If
        Set scan_i to scan_i plus 1
    End While
End Process

Note: Append text followed by a newline. Equivalent to emit(text) +
Note: emit_newline.
Process called "emitter_emit_line" takes ctx as EmitterContext, text as String:
    proc emitter_emit with ctx, text
    proc emitter_emit_newline with ctx
End Process

Note: Append a newline byte. Updates the line counter and sets line_start
Note: so the next emit re-applies indentation.
Process called "emitter_emit_newline" takes ctx as EmitterContext:
    proc emitter_ctx_emit_byte with ctx, EMITTER_NEWLINE_BYTE
    Set ctx.current_line to ctx.current_line plus 1
    Set ctx.current_column to 1
    Set ctx.line_start to 1
End Process

Note: Append a single space byte without affecting line state.
Process called "emitter_emit_space" takes ctx as EmitterContext:
    proc emitter_ctx_emit_byte with ctx, EMITTER_SPACE_BYTE
    Set ctx.current_column to ctx.current_column plus 1
    Set ctx.line_start to 0
End Process

Note: Append a blank line (bare newline with no preceding indent). Useful
Note: between top-level declarations.
Process called "emitter_emit_blank_line" takes ctx as EmitterContext:
    proc emitter_emit_newline with ctx
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ERROR AND WARNING TRACKING
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Record an error message. Sets had_error.
Process called "emitter_error" takes ctx as EmitterContext, message as String:
    proc list_append from ListCore with ctx.errors, message
    Set ctx.had_error to 1
End Process

Note: Record a non-fatal warning. Does not set had_error.
Process called "emitter_warning" takes ctx as EmitterContext, message as String:
    proc list_append from ListCore with ctx.warnings, message
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: OUTPUT ACCESS
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Return the accumulated output as a null-terminated String. The
Note: returned pointer is freshly allocated and owned by the caller.
Process called "emitter_get_output" takes ctx as EmitterContext returns String:
    If ctx.output_buffer is equal to 0:
        Return ""
    End If

    Let output be proc allocate from Layout with ctx.output_length plus 1
    If output is equal to 0:
        Return ""
    End If

    If ctx.output_length is greater than 0:
        proc memory_copy from MemoryCore with output, ctx.output_buffer, ctx.output_length
    End If
    proc memory_set_byte from MemoryCore with output, ctx.output_length, 0
    Return output
End Process

Note: True if any error was recorded.
Process called "emitter_has_errors" takes ctx as EmitterContext returns Integer:
    Return ctx.had_error
End Process

Note: Return the recorded error list.
Process called "emitter_get_errors" takes ctx as EmitterContext returns List[String]:
    Return ctx.errors
End Process

Note: Return the recorded warning list.
Process called "emitter_get_warnings" takes ctx as EmitterContext returns List[String]:
    Return ctx.warnings
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: RESET
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Reset all state in-place so a single context can be reused across
Note: multiple translation invocations without reallocating the byte buffer.
Process called "emitter_reset" takes ctx as EmitterContext:
    Set ctx.output_length to 0
    Set ctx.indent_level to 0
    Set ctx.current_line to 1
    Set ctx.current_column to 1
    Set ctx.line_start to 1
    Set ctx.had_error to 0
    Set ctx.errors to proc list_create from ListCore
    Set ctx.warnings to proc list_create from ListCore
End Process
